<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Moriendor on 05-05-2002 02:04 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Anthea: &gt;&gt;[i]- If I have a special type of potion no more, it is still shown in the "browse potions" icons[/i]&lt;&lt;

I think this is OK. Look at the potion symbol very closely and you should see that it has changed its color to transparent, thus indicating an empty flask, i.e. you just don't have anymore potions of that type.

Some more things I noticed:

1) Why does Grugar, the zombie, attack the orcs around Smiruk? Seems like a logical bug. If I am neutral towards them then Grugar should not attack them either.

2) It is at times difficult to tell whether a stairway in the dungeons leads up or down.

3) It sometimes says "Stairway" on e.g. the 2nd level of the dungeon whereas when you're on 3rd level, facing the exact same "stairway" it's called "iron ladder". Maybe, to keep it consistent, it might be a good idea to call it the same on both levels.

4) Had an item bug. My character had an agility of over 15 but I could not use an item that required a min. agility of 15. The text was red on the item description, indicating I can't use it. However, as I was keeping the mouse pointer over the item for a longer time, the font color suddenly changed back to normal and I could also equip the item again.

5) Why does the mini map keep on disappearing when you change levels? It's sort of annyoing when you always have to hit the "M" key after changing locations.

6) This may be my own fault but am I correct in assuming that the trade window always disappears after a successful deal? Why? I sometimes want to trade first, then get stuff repaired or identified. It's tedious when you have to start the dialogue over and over again.

7) Goemoe will be very happy because there is no "oink" sound when a spider mine is chasing the character  :) . In fact, there's no sound at all. I got killed a few times just because I didn't hear the mines and once you see them it's too late  ;) .

8) When you zoom out of the overview map you can see note flags you have placed on previous levels. Makes it a little confusing.

9) The two center tombs in the catacombs still said "locked" even though they were open.

10) In the lower levels of the catacombs with the blue windows it's sometimes hard to spot your character on the overview map. Maybe it'd be a good idea to make the small blue char spot a little bigger or let it flash up.

11) When someone says "I'll...." in dialogues or manuscripts it looks strange like "III" due to the font. Maybe you should write it out, i.e. "I will...".

12) In general, it would be great if you could move levers only once. I really hate it when I have no clue what the default position of a lever was and it makes it easier to determine whether you've already used a lever or not.

------------------
Moriendor
Editor @ [URL=http://www.rpgdot.com/]RPGDot[/URL]
Webmaster @ [URL=http://www.divinity-the-sword-of-lies.com]Divinity-The-Sword-Of-Lies.com[/URL]</TEXTAREA>
